  <description><![CDATA[<p>The stylish Modica Beach Resort provides a great base for exploring this fascinating corner of <a data-udi="umb://document/aafdbd88af954166b49b0bd7fa839f19" href="/{localLink:umb://document/aafdbd88af954166b49b0bd7fa839f19}" title="South East Sicily">Sicily</a>. Located a short walk (10-15 minutes) from the small town of Marina de Modica, overlooking the sea and just a twenty-five minute drive from the buzzing medieval city of <em>Modica</em>, with its beautiful baroque buildings. The hotels private beach is close by. Relax on the comfortable padded loungers at this calm beachside oasis under the shade of a parasol or wooden gazebo, before taking a dip in the crystal-clear waters. Listen to the waves lap the shore and feel the cool sea breeze wash over you as you soak up the Sicilian sun. The beachside bar offers cool and refreshing drinks and the Le Dune restaurant serves a light lunch, so you’ll be fully equipped for a relaxing day on the beach.</p>
<p>On the large terrace before the dunes is the beach restaurant serving traditional, gourmet, Sicilian cuisine, with a fantastic sea view as a backdrop. The modern rooms are decorated in light sandy tones giving them a fresh and breezy seaside feel. If the idyllic setting alone is not enough to get you feeling relaxed then head over to the Wellness Centre to enjoy a soothing massage (payable locally). This is the perfect place to relax and unwind, whist being in a great location to explore the region and learn about Sicilian history and culture.</p>]]></description>
